
add server:
    yarn add server

now we can serve the project on web
    yarn serve

created dockerfile and docker-compose to start the server.

to run services
---------------
Run container:
    docker-compose up web
    
Now I can login while container is running:
    docker exec -it $(docker ps -q) /bin/bash
    (replace with container ID if needed)


building app
------------

add typescript:
    yarn add typescript --dev
    yarn run tsc --init

build folder and perm:
    mkdir build
    chmod 775 build
    sudo chmod 775 tsconfig.json
    sudo chown jj tsconfig.json

modify tsconfig.json with watch options in article:
    https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/configuring-watch.html

add exclude:
    "exclude": [
        "node_modules",
        "**/*.spec.ts"
    ]

------------------------------------------
run ts transpiler
-----------------
this does not really work at building modules though, so use webpack instead

after yarn server starts up, watch source for transpiling by opening a new container:

    docker exec -it $(docker ps -q) /bin/bash

    (in container)
        yarn run tsc --watch



-------------------------------------------
add webpack
-----------
container 'web' must be running
    docker-compose up web

open new container for shell into container 'web'
    docker exec -it $(docker ps -q) /bin/bash

    (in container)
        yarn add webpack webpack-cli --dev
    
follow beginner tutorial to put index.html into new folder dist/
    https://webpack.js.org/guides/getting-started/

    dist/index.html will have link to the build like so:
        <script src="/dist/main.js"></script>
